{{Infobox Song Contest |name = Beovizija |year=2007 |semi= 7 March|final=8 March |presenters=[[Jelena Jovičić]] and [[Slobodan Ninković|Boda Ninković]] |venue=Sava Center, [[Belgrade]], [[Serbia]] |winner=[[Molitva]] |vote=50% Jury and 50% Televoting |entries=20 competing songs |interval=[[Flamingosi]] feat. [[Louis (singer)|Luis]], [[Stevan Faddy]], [[Dado Topić]] feat. [[Dragonfly]], [[Alenka Gotar]], [[Marija Šestić]], [[Karolina Gočeva]] }} '''Beovizija 2007''' was the 5th edition of [[Beovizija]] and the first national selection for the newly independent [[Serbia]] in the [[Eurovision Song Contest]]. It was held on 7 March (semi-finals) and 8 March (finals). The winner of the contest, [[Marija Šerifović]], represented Serbia in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2007]] in [[Helsinki]], and came away as overall winner of the competition.
