{{Multiple issues| {{refimprove|date=December 2012}}{{notability|Music|date=October 2012}}}} {{Infobox musical artist | name = Cheek Mountain Thief | image = | image_size = | landscape = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank --> | alt = | caption = | background = group_or_band | alias = | origin = [[Húsavík]] and [[Reykjavík]], Iceland | genre = [[Indie rock]] | years_active = {{start date|2011}}–present | label = [[Full Time Hobby]] | associated_acts = [[Tunng]] | website = {{URL|http://www.cheekmountainthief.co.uk/}} | current_members = Mike Lindsay | past_members = }}
'''Cheek Mountain Thief''' is a project started in 2011 by Mike Lindsay, founding member of the UK twisted acid folk band [[Tunng]]. He lives in [[Iceland]] where he formed a band with musicians from [[Húsavík]] and [[Reykjavík]].
Lindsay said that his love affair with Iceland began in 2006. It involved a girl, Harpa, and an unforgettable New Year’s Eve party. In 2011, Lindsay returned to Iceland to rekindle that romance, and to record a new album under the name Cheek Mountain Thief, inspired by the landscape and the people of Iceland.<ref name=sheppard>{{cite web|last=Hampson|first=Gemma|title=A splash of Icelandic charm|url=http://www.clashmusic.com/live-review/cheek-mountain-thief-live-at-purcell-room-london|publisher=clashmusic.com|accessdate=13 September 2012|date=5 August 2011}}</ref>
The band is signed on the London independent record label [[Full Time Hobby]].
== Discography == Their first album received good reviews.<ref name=woodcraft>{{cite web|last=Woodcraft|first=Molloy|title=Cheek Mountain Thief – review|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2012/aug/12/cheek-mountain-thief-tunng-review|publisher=guardian.co.uk|accessdate=12 August 2012|date=5 August 2011}}</ref><ref name=Seban>{{cite web|last=Seban|first=Johanna|title=Cheek Mountain Thief : un trésor de la rentrée|url=http://www.lesinrocks.com/musique/critique-album/cheek-mountain-un-tresor-de-la-rentree/|publisher=lesinrocks.com|accessdate=13 September 2012|date=5 August 2011}}</ref>
