The '''Electoral Commission of Namibia''' ('''ECN''') is an agency of the [[Government of Namibia]].<ref name="GovIndex">{{cite web |url=http://209.88.21.36/opencms/opencms/grnnet/GRNOverview2/CetralGov.html |archive-url=https://archive.is/20121129185603/http://209.88.21.36/opencms/opencms/grnnet/GRNOverview2/CetralGov.html |dead-url=yes |archive-date=29 November 2012 |title=A-Z Index of Central Government |publisher=Office of the Prime Minister |accessdate=29 September 2011 }}</ref> It was founded in 1992 under the Electoral Act #24 of 1992. The aim of the commission is to oversee all electoral activities starting from [[voter registration]] and political party registration, to the setting and monitoring of elections, counting of ballots and making results available.<ref name=ecn>[http://www.ecn.na/about.html About us] ''ECN official website'', retrieved 19 February 2012</ref>
The ECN is composed of a chairperson and four commissioners. Candidates are shortlisted by a committee consisting of the [[Chief Justice of Namibia|Chief Justice]], a lawyer suggested by the [[Law Society of Namibia|Law Society]] and a representative from the [[Ombudsman (Namibia)|Office of the Ombudsman]]. The [[President of Namibia]] then appoints the ECN from this shortlist for a five-year term.<ref name=ecn/>
The {{As of|2009|alt=current}} Director of Elections is [[Moses Ndjarakana]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.electionwatch.org.na/node/368 |title=Election Watch: The tendered vote controversy, again |publisher=Institute for Public Policy Research |accessdate=19 February 2012}}</ref>
==See also== * [[Politics of Namibia]] * [[List of political parties in Namibia]]
