'''Mersch communal council''' ({{lang-fr|Conseil communal de Mersch}}) is the [[Local government|local council]] for the [[Communes of Luxembourg|commune]] of [[Mersch]], in central [[Luxembourg]].
It consists of thirteen members, elected every six years by [[proportional representation]].<ref name="Conseil Communal">{{cite web|url=http://www.mersch.lu/Default.aspx?id=f5f2f902-06d0-489a-bc16-4fe2e3ee5e9b |title=Conseil Communal |accessdate=2007-09-24 |date= |publisher=Commune of Kayl |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070610110901/http://www.mersch.lu/Default.aspx?id=f5f2f902-06d0-489a-bc16-4fe2e3ee5e9b |archivedate=2007-06-10 |language=fr |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> The last elections were held on 9 October 2005, and resulted in a draw between the [[Democratic Party (Luxembourg)|Democratic Party]] (DP) and the [[Christian Social People's Party]] (CSV). In the ''[[Collège échevinal (Luxembourg)|collège échevinal]]'', the DP and CSV form a coalition under the leadership of DP [[Mayor of Mersch|mayor]] [[Albert Henkel]].<ref name="Conseil Communal" />
