{{Orphan|date=October 2017}}

'''Mofo Gasy''', translated as "Malagasy bread", is a [[Madagascar|Malagasy]] traditional recipe typically eaten as a breakfast. It consists mainly of rice flour<ref>{{cite book | last=LeHoullier | first=S. | title=Madagascar (Travel Companion) | publisher=Other Places Publishing | year=2010 | isbn=978-0-9822619-5-8 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QhAbnvPKaVUC&pg=PA124 | accessdate=January 12, 2017 | page=124}}</ref> and sugar fried within a specific mold. Mofo gasy can also be made with coconut milk. Variations of the recipe occur based on the regions of Madagascar.

