{{Politics of Benin}}
'''National Party "Together"''' ({{Lang-fr|Parti National Ensemble}}) is a political party in [[Benin]] led by [[Albert Teveodjré]]. PNE was formed following a split in [[Our Common Cause]] (NCC).

PNE was legally recognized on August 11, 1998.

PNE maintains relations with [[Conservatism|conservative]] and [[Christian Democratic]] groups abroad. In 2002, it received a grant from the [[Konrad Adenauer Foundation]] (linked to [[Germany|German]] [[Christian Democratic Union (Germany)|CDU]]) to organize a youth camp.

