{{Expand Italian|Diocesi di Kericho|date=February 2011}} {{Infobox diocese |jurisdiction = Diocese |name = Kericho |latin = Dioecesis Kerichoensis |country = {{flag|Kenya}} |metropolitan = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Nairobi|Nairobi]] |rite = [[Latin Rite]] |cathedral = |cocathedral = |area_km2 = 4,800 |population = 1,554,850 |population_as_of = 2004 |catholics = 223,856 |catholics_percent= 14.4 |pope = {{Incumbent pope}} |bishop = [[Rt. Rev. Emmanuel Wandera Okombo]] |coadjutor = |auxiliary_bishops= }}
The '''Roman Catholic Diocese of Kericho''' ({{lang-la|Kerichoën(sis)}}) is a [[diocese]] located in the city of [[Kericho]] in the [[Ecclesiastical province]] of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Nairobi|Nairobi]] in [[Kenya]].
==History== * December 6, 1995: Established as Diocese of Kericho from the [[Diocese of Nakuru]]. The Diocese has 42 parishes with various religious institutions, congregations, schools, hospitals, health centers, projects and programmes.
==Leadership== * [[Bishop]]s of Kericho (Roman rite) ** Bishop Emmanuel Okombo (since March 22, 2003) ** Bishop [[Philip Arnold Subira Anyolo]] (December 6, 1995 – March 22, 2003)
==Staff== * Vicar General: Father Samuel Karanja * Vocation Director: Father David K. Cheruiyot * Youth Coordinator: Father Leonard K. Bett * Liturgical Coordinator: Father Patrick Koech * Procurator: Father Ibrahim Nyang'ate * Education Secretary: Father James Etiyat * Catechetical Coordinator: Father Simon Rono * CJPC Coordinator (Volunteer): Mr Kipkorir Tesot * Caritas Director/Development Coordinator(Volunteer): Mr Bernard K. Sawe * Health Coordinator(Volunteer): Mr John Lang'at * PMC Coordinator: Father Daniel Kiprono Cheruiyot
==See also== *[[Roman Catholicism in Kenya]]
