[[File:Wahlkreis Uuvudhiya in Oshana.png|right|thumb|Uuvudhiya Constituency (yellow) in the Oshana Region (dark grey)]]
'''Uuvudhiya Constituency''' is an [[Constituencies of Namibia|electoral constituency]] in the [[Oshana Region]] of [[Namibia]]. It has 4,357 inhabitants,<ref>[http://www.statoids.com/yna.html Constituencies of Namibia, 2004]</ref> its district capital is the settlement of [[Uuvudhiya]]. The constituency had 2,869 registered voters as of 2004.<ref>[http://www.ecn.gov.na/RUuvudhiya.htm Uuvudhiya Constituency]. Namibia Electoral Commission. 2004. Retrieved on March 24, 2008.</ref>
==Geography== [[Lake Oponona]], the largest lake in the [[Cuvelai Basin]], is situated in Uuvudhiya Constituency.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.newera.com.na/features/stricken-cattle-threaten-lake/ |title=Stricken cattle threaten lake |last=Shaanika |first=Helvy |work=[[New Era (Namibia)|New Era]] |date=30 August 2013}}</ref>
==Politics== Uuvudhiya constituency is traditionally a stronghold of the [[South West Africa People's Organization]] (SWAPO) party.
In the [[Namibian local and regional elections, 2010|2010 regional elections]], [[SWAPO]]'s [[Seblon Paulus]] won the constituency with 1,621 votes. His only challenger was Gabriel SH. Jeremia of the [[Rally for Democracy and Progress (Namibia)|Rally for Democracy and Progress]], who received 19 votes.<ref>[http://www.ecn.na/results/2010/Press_Release_Constituency_-_Oshana-Uuvudhiya.pdf Results from the Electoral Commission of Namibia]</ref> In the [[Namibian local and regional elections, 2015|2015 local and regional elections]] the SWAPO candidate won uncontested and became councillor after no opposition party nominated a candidate.<ref name=uncontested>{{cite news|last=Kangootui |first=Nomhle |newspaper=[[The Namibian]] |title=Swapo gets ǃNamiǂNûs uncontested |url=http://www.namibian.com.na/index.php?page=read&id=33153 |date=23 October 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151024163513/http://www.namibian.com.na/index.php?page=read&id=33153 |archivedate=October 24, 2015 }}</ref>
